    <h1 class="heading1">General Surgery Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our General Surgery Department offers a wide range of surgical services to address diverse medical conditions, from routine procedures to complex surgeries. Led by a team of skilled surgeons and healthcare professionals, we are committed to providing high-quality surgical care, utilizing advanced techniques and state-of-the-art facilities to ensure the best possible outcomes for our patients.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Minimally Invasive Surgery</h4>
            <p>We specialize in minimally invasive surgical techniques, including laparoscopic and robotic-assisted surgeries, which offer several advantages over traditional open surgery, such as smaller incisions, reduced pain, shorter hospital stays, and faster recovery times. Our surgeons are highly skilled in performing minimally invasive procedures for various conditions, including gallbladder disease, hernias, appendicitis, and colorectal disorders.</p>

            <h4>General Surgical Procedures</h4>
            <p>We offer a comprehensive range of general surgical procedures to treat conditions affecting the abdomen, gastrointestinal tract, endocrine system, breast, skin, and soft tissues. Our surgeons are experienced in performing surgeries such as appendectomy, cholecystectomy, colectomy, gastrectomy, thyroidectomy, mastectomy, and skin lesion excision, utilizing advanced surgical techniques to achieve optimal outcomes for our patients.</p>

            <h4>Emergency Surgery</h4>
            <p>Our General Surgery Department provides emergency surgical services for patients with acute surgical conditions, such as trauma, perforated organs, bowel obstructions, and acute appendicitis. Our surgical team is available 24/7 to respond to emergencies, providing timely evaluation, diagnosis, and surgical intervention to stabilize patients and prevent further complications.</p>

            <h4>Trauma Surgery</h4>
            <p>We have expertise in trauma surgery to care for patients with traumatic injuries, including blunt trauma, penetrating injuries, and multisystem trauma. Our trauma surgeons are trained to assess and manage traumatic injuries involving the chest, abdomen, pelvis, and extremities, providing rapid resuscitation, surgical intervention, and critical care support in our trauma center.</p>

            <h4>Oncologic Surgery</h4>
            <p>We offer surgical treatment for various cancers, including gastrointestinal cancers, breast cancer, skin cancer, and soft tissue sarcomas. Our surgical oncologists collaborate closely with oncologists, radiation oncologists, and other specialists to develop comprehensive treatment plans tailored to each patient's specific cancer type, stage, and individual needs, aiming for optimal cancer control and quality of life.</p>

            <h4>Postoperative Care</h4>
            <p>Our General Surgery Department provides comprehensive postoperative care to support patients through the recovery process following surgery. Our multidisciplinary team of surgeons, nurses, and allied healthcare professionals monitor patients closely, manage pain, prevent complications, and provide education and support to facilitate a smooth and successful recovery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
